Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.69,0:03:14.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the 37th year of Meiji (1904),
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.95,0:03:20.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Japan faced an unprecedented national crisis\N in the face of Imperial Russia's Far Eastern policy.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.70,0:03:30.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Russian aggression in Manchuria exerted increasing pressure on Japan, and the anger of the entire nation reached its peak.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.35,0:03:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Sino-Japanese War, the Liaodong Peninsula at the southern end of Manchuria became Japanese territory,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:39.34,0:03:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,yet our possession of the peninsula was declared a threat to world peace and we were forced to return it to Qing China
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.85,0:03:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,by Russia, who led the so-called Triple Intervention.{dc: cps}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.39,0:03:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Russia forcibly leased \Nthe Liaodong Peninsula from China,{dc: cps}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.15,0:03:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,constructed a new city, Dalny, and is building fortifications at Port Arthur, all for what, exactly?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.73,0:04:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.01,0:04:07.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, seven doctors—Imperial University professors Tomizu, Terao, Onozuka, Kanai, Nakamura, Takahashi, and Tomii— {https://www.japanesewiki.com/history/Shichihakushi%20Ikensho%20(seven%20doctors%20opinion).html}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.07,0:04:13.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,condemned Russia for violating international law{dc: what's new there} and petitioned the government to take a stance against Russia.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.07,0:04:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of that, Russia used \Nthe Boxer Uprising of 1900 as an excuse
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.45,0:04:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and refused to withdraw the troops it had dispatched.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.12,0:04:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead they have steadily built up in Manchuria, strengthening its military position,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.96,0:04:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and now appears intent \Non extending its power into Korea.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.41,0:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall it be ruin, or war?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.36,0:04:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Japan simply allow itself \Nto become prey to Russia's Far Eastern policy,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.83,0:04:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or will the people unite as one \Nand face this national crisis?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.30,0:04:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer depends entirely upon the resolve of you, \Nthe citizens of this nation.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.59,0:04:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Foreign Minister Komura has met more than a dozen times with
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.78,0:04:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Minister Rosen of Russia, \Nand now the truth of the matter is clear. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman_Rosen}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.21,0:04:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia's attitude {in the Russo-Japanese negotiations }shows not the slightest trace of sincerity!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.45,0:04:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If we permit Russia's tyranny to continue unchecked,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.72,0:05:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it is as clear as day that Japan will eventually \Nfall victim to its Far Eastern ambitions!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.56,0:05:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand firm against this national crisis!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.83,0:05:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Crush Russia's arrogance!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.60,0:05:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.56,0:05:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Defend our two thousand years of history!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.80,0:05:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do not fight now, Japan will perish!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.60,0:05:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.65,0:05:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Every man, take up arms!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.86,0:05:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.38,0:06:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As the situation with Russia \Nhas become so critical,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.97,0:06:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we have no choice \Nbut to take measures of self-defense.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.47,0:06:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia's army and navy are three times \Nthe strength of Japan's current forces,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.91,0:06:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but our military has taken every precaution \Nand stands ready to mobilize at any time.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.33,0:06:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At this Imperial Conference today, \Nwe wish to arrive at a final decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.27,0:06:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As Acting Prime Minister Yamamoto has just stated, {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yamamoto_Gonnohy%C5%8De}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.26,0:06:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,our nation has forty million people, \Nwhile Russia has four hundred million. {think they inflated numbers for some reason? ain't no way that true, not even with poland finland and all of -stans; maybe I'm just hearing it all wrong?}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.73,0:06:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Their army prides itself on great strength \Nand is by no means an opponent to be taken lightly,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.51,0:07:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but our people have already steeled themselves \Nto face this national crisis.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.78,0:07:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We now humbly await Your Majesty's final judgment.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.47,0:07:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, there seems to be no choice \Nbut to seize the initiative and take action in self-defense.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.57,0:07:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If we continue to hesitate and merely declare the facts, \Nwe will only allow Russia to further strengthen its war preparations
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.57,0:07:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and aid it in achieving its ambitions.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.15,0:07:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As for our finances, even judging \Nfrom the experience of the Sino-Japanese War,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.28,0:07:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,adjusting them as circumstances develop \Nwill not be difficult.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.70,0:07:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How do the nations of the world \Nview the issue between Japan and Russia?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.23,0:07:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from those countries \Nwith special interests in Russia,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.66,0:07:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,almost all resent Russia's aggression \Nand sympathize with Japan's predicament.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.95,0:08:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, since Russia is the strongest land power in the world, \Nmost believe Japan has no hope of standing against it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.04,0:08:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the United States and our ally Great Britain—\Nas the Finance Minister will soon explain—
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.68,0:08:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,have shown our country extremely active goodwill.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.96,0:08:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The war chest is estimated \Nat approximately 450 million yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.39,0:08:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Of this amount, foreign expenditures will total 150 million yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.83,0:08:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Of that sum, 50 million yen \Nwill be paid using gold held by the Bank of Japan,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.70,0:08:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we are confident the remaining 100 million \Ncan be borrowed in Britain and America.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.60,0:08:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How far into the war does that estimate extend?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.34,0:08:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,After consultation with the Army General Staff and the Naval Command, \Nwe roughly estimate one year.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.89,0:08:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the war continues for two or three years?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.23,0:08:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll dispatch Bank of Japan \NVice Governor Takahashi Korekiyo {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Takahashi_Korekiyo}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:57.63,0:09:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to the United States and Britain \Nto devote all efforts to securing foreign loans.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.18,0:09:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As Chairman Ito has already stated, if the entire nation \Nstakes both life and property and rises to the challenge, {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/It%C5%8D_Hirobumi}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.94,0:09:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I am convinced we can overcome this national crisis.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.99,0:09:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How are Yamamoto's and Katsura's illnesses? {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katsura_Tar%C5%8D / https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yamamoto_Gonnohy%C5%8De }
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.85,0:09:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the Prime Minister forced himself \Nto attend the gathering despite his illness,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.86,0:09:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but he had to withdraw as the pain became too much.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.87,0:09:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there truly no room left for negotiations with Russia?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.21,0:09:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Things remain as they were after Foreign Minister Komura and Minister Rosen's fourteenth meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.19,0:09:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They proposed recognizing the region \Nnorth of Pyongyang as a neutral zone, did they not?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.46,0:09:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That proposal was effectively \Na blade turned against Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.25,0:10:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We notified them that it absolutely must be withdrawn, \Nbut we have received no reply.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.80,0:10:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we accept this humiliation without an answer, \Nthe people will surely lose their trust in the government.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.62,0:10:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be wise to consider once more, \Ncarefully, whether a path to a breakthrough remains.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.73,0:10:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty's will is that we once again \Nseek resolution with Russia?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.16,0:10:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This decision will be the final one.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.86,0:10:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider well
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.63,0:10:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,how it will be received by the people,\Nand do everything possible to avoid war.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.15,0:10:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We humbly obey Your Majesty's will.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.29,0:10:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, shall today's conference be adjourned here?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.03,0:11:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You have all done well.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.43,0:11:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.12,0:11:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait a moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.64,0:11:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The elder statesmen have already decided upon war.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.30,0:11:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty, please wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.60,0:11:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The meeting has been adjourned.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.53,0:11:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back to your seat! {???? the script says "押さえなさい。" = hold it back - hold back what? that guy? why are they all walking backwards after this?}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.16,0:11:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Minister Yamamoto,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.48,0:11:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,your actions violate an imperial command.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.03,0:11:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this Prime Minister Katsura's doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.22,0:11:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What? I won't tolerate any talk \Nof me disobeying the Emperor's will!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.76,0:11:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragging Prime Minister Katsura \Ninto this is most improper.{dc: i can't do shit about this line}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.56,0:11:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen well.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.40,0:11:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The council of elder statesmen called for war this morning—you even said so!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.58,0:11:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet when I attempted to report that decision, \Nyou blocked me in that chamber.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.17,0:12:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only conclude that your action \Ndistorted His Majesty's will!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.76,0:12:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.76,0:12:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself never expected the words \NHis Majesty spoke today.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.32,0:12:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you truly hear what His Majesty \Nsaid at that moment?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.79,0:12:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Since this conference is the final and highest council,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.43,0:12:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,one mistake could drag the nation into the suffering of war
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.13,0:12:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and even threaten the very existence of Japan!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.40,0:12:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Though it be presumptuous, daresay \NI understand His Majesty's feelings.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:29.89,0:12:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If there remains any possibility of avoiding war, His Majesty’s will was that we should open a path to a peaceful resolution.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.91,0:12:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In those few brief words,\NI am convinced that is what he meant!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.75,0:12:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Inoue-san, in truth, I too was deeply moved \Nby His Majesty’s words today.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.72,0:12:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed clear that war pains His Majesty \Nmore than if his own body were cut.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.24,0:13:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I failed to grasp the depth of His Majesty’s feelings.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.31,0:13:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That was my failing.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.42,0:13:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I must offer my apology to His Majesty.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.49,0:13:21.62,Song,,0,0,0,,Though all the seas {found this: https://note.com/emo_matsuishi/n/n7712f3290b1e }
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.62,0:13:32.63,Song,,0,0,0,,in every direction are thought to be born of one kin,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.63,0:13:43.11,Song,,0,0,0,,why then do the winds and waves
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.11,0:13:57.39,Song,,0,0,0,,rise and rage against one another?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.47,0:14:05.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yet Russia failed to reply, ignoring Japan's proposal for compromise,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.87,0:14:12.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and instead crossed the Korean border with massive forces.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.24,0:14:18.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At Port Arthur, at the tip of the Liaodong Peninsula, \Nthey had nearly completed an impregnable fortress.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.75,0:14:24.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The commander of that fortress \Nwas one of Russia's foremost generals, Stessel. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anatoly_Stessel}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.08,0:14:59.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even by February 3rd, no reply had come from Russia.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.07,0:15:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister Katsura, never have our people
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.93,0:15:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,thoroughly examined the Russian question and earnestly debated whether war is right or wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.93,0:15:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,By now every argument has been exhausted, and opposition to war \Nhas all but disappeared—you must be aware of that!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.44,0:15:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The government, for its part, has already made concessions to Russia to the fullest extent,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.81,0:15:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,yet still no answer has come from Russia.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.31,0:15:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It is clear that Russia's aim is to crush Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.08,0:15:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Even while Japan's independence itself is in danger, \Ndo you still intend to avoid war?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.35,0:15:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To avoid war as far as possible \Nis the deep wish of His Majesty.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.21,0:15:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,His Majesty's intention?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.29,0:15:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.58,0:15:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe His Majesty cannot bear to see tens of thousands of precious lives once again sacrificed on the wild plains of Manchuria.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.15,0:15:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The hour for the meeting has come. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.23,0:16:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:03.40,0:16:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I am about to attend the national assembly, \Nbut I would like to hear the military's position regarding Russia. {was positive views, but that sounds incorrect}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.36,0:16:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The question of whether we should go to war \Nis not something the military should debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.39,0:16:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Yamamoto?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.58,0:16:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's convening with Dr. Tomita \Nand others at the Cabinet. {most likely https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/200613804/masaakira-tomii but here and later they clearly call him tomiza/tomita... i wonder why}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.60,0:16:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tomita will report on the results of his meetings \Nwith Prime Minister Katsura and the other ministers.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.98,0:16:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time of unprecedented national crisis, \Nit appears the government too is prepared for grave decisions.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.72,0:17:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as for His Majesty, if war breaks out, \Nyour brothers will all become tragic sacrifices,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.71,0:17:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is said His Majesty is deeply troubled by this thought,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.29,0:17:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as by the suffering that war \Nwill bring upon the lives of the people at home.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.30,0:17:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, Naval Minister Yamamoto \Nwas preparing to attend an important meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:26.38,0:17:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To transport the army's large forces to the continent,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.40,0:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we must divide the enemy's Far Eastern fleet \Nbetween Vladivostok and Port Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.77,0:17:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, their new fortress at Port Arthur is an excellent naval base overlooking the landing points of our transports.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.18,0:17:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, blockading Port Arthur is an absolute necessity.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.32,0:17:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We will scuttle some ships at the entrance to the harbor, \Nand if this blockade can be carried out completely,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.89,0:17:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the enemy will be trapped inside Port Arthur like rats in a sack,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.16,0:17:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,losing its function as a base, leaving Vladivostok \Nas the enemy's only base in the Far East.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:57.26,0:18:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But is it really possible to sink several ships like that?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.07,0:18:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even sinking a single vessel caused great confusion during the attempt to block Santiago Harbor in the Spanish-American War. {meaning the americans didn't know how to do it right and botched it}{dc: story of my life}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.58,0:18:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,With the training our navy conducts every day, \Nit should not be impossible.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.93,0:18:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If the worst should come, \Nwe will take off these coats, take off our shoes,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.09,0:18:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,turn everything we have into shells \Nand rifles, and send them to the front!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.72,0:18:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And if even that is not enough, \Nwe will stand behind the lines ourselves!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.26,0:18:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We must fight Russia's Far Eastern policy \Nwith absolute determination!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.05,0:18:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter if the enemy outnumbers us many times over, \Nif we do not drive them back, Japan will become their slave forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.96,0:18:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The movements of each fleet \Nwill proceed roughly as described.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:50.93,0:18:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And at tomorrow's Imperial Conference, \NI believe all matters will be finally decided.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.01,0:19:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Excellency, any further patience \Nand restraint will only benefit Russia.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.69,0:19:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you to firmly advocate the opening of war.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.40,0:19:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten a soldier's duty?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.53,0:19:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not interfere in politics.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.29,0:19:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.62,0:19:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:13.57,0:19:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,An emergency cabinet meeting has been called.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.88,0:19:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What has happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.31,0:19:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The fleets from Vladivostok and Port Arthur both left at five this morning in battle formation,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.35,0:19:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and their destination is unknown.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.94,0:19:41.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On February 4th, the Imperial Conference \Nthat would decide the fate of the nation was convened.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.62,0:19:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Every possible issue between Japan and Russia \Nhas been thoroughly examined,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.18,0:19:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and we now humbly await Your Majesty's decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.28,0:19:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there truly no way to avoid war?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.46,0:20:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At this stage, there is none.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.69,0:20:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We carefully considered Your Majesty's feelings \Nfrom at the previous Imperial Conference.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.53,0:20:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The people, down to the very last man, are crying that they will throw everything they have into the fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.41,0:20:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the opinion of the Diet?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.02,0:20:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Both houses have resolved in favor of war.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.22,0:20:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If the worst should happen,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.49,0:20:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we could not face our imperial ancestors
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.96,0:20:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,nor the forty million people of this nation.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.44,0:20:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.31,0:20:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The elder statesmen and the cabinet, \Nand the Diet representing the people as well,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.10,0:20:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,have all concluded that war is unavoidable.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.76,0:21:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I approve the severing of diplomatic relations.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.19,0:21:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Extra! Extra!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.53,0:21:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Extra! Extra! Extra!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.86,0:21:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Diplomatic relations! \NDiplomatic relations severed!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.60,0:21:59.47,Song,,0,0,0,,To smite injustice in Heaven’s name, {天に代わりて不義を討つ\N忠勇無雙の我が兵は\N歡呼の聲に送られて\N今ぞ出で立つ父母の國\N勝たつば生きて還(かえ)らじと\N誓う心の勇ましさ}{https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E9%99%B8%E8%BB%8D_(%E8%BB%8D%E6%AD%8C) - the song is subdivided into verses, dedicated to one branch of the army; first one is "Going to war"}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.47,0:22:03.41,Song,,0,0,0,,Our soldiers—peerless in loyal courage—
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.41,0:22:11.18,Song,,0,0,0,,Amid the people’s cheering cries \NNow march forth from the land of their fathers and mothers
Dialogue: 10,0:22:11.18,0:22:14.86,Song,,0,0,0,,Sworn that if we do not win,\NAlive we shall not return—
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.86,0:22:18.93,Song,,0,0,0,,How valiant is the heart that swears it! {honestly the audio is so shit that I have no idea where one line starts and the other ends or even what part of the lyrics is being sung currently}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.93,0:22:26.80,Song,,0,0,0,,Some lie hidden in the grass,\NOthers plunge into the water; {second verse - "scout soldier": 或いは草に伏し隱れ\N或いは水に飛び入りて\N萬死恐れず敵情を\N視察し歸る斥候兵\N肩に懸(かか)れる一軍の\N安危はいかに重からん}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:26.80,0:22:34.81,Song,,0,0,0,,Braving death a thousand times,\NThe scouts return from watching the foe
Dialogue: 10,0:22:34.81,0:22:43.02,Song,,0,0,0,,On their shoulders rests the safety of the whole army—\NHow heavy is that charge!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:46.65,0:22:50.66,Song,,0,0,0,,{third verse - "engineer": 道なき方(かた)に道をつけ\N敵の鐵道うち毀(こぼ)ち\N雨と散り來る彈丸を\N身に浴びながら橋かけて\N我が軍渡す工兵の\N功勞何にか譬(たと)うべき}Where no road runs, they carve a road,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:49.98,0:22:56.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, the elite units of the army, under the escort of the navy, \Ncarried out their landing operations.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:50.66,0:22:54.43,Song,,0,0,0,,They smash the enemy’s railways;
Dialogue: 10,0:22:54.43,0:22:58.33,Song,,0,0,0,,While bullets fall like driving rain
Dialogue: 10,0:22:56.50,0:23:00.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then marched north across the snowy wilderness, \Ninto southern Manchuria.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:58.33,0:23:02.17,Song,,0,0,0,,They bathe in fire and build the bridges
Dialogue: 10,0:23:02.17,0:23:06.17,Song,,0,0,0,,That let our army cross—
Dialogue: 10,0:23:06.17,0:23:10.21,Song,,0,0,0,,What could compare with the merits of those engineers?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:10.21,0:23:14.05,Song,,0,0,0,,To smite injustice in Heaven’s name, {first verse again}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:14.05,0:23:17.85,Song,,0,0,0,,Our soldiers—peerless in loyal courage—
Dialogue: 10,0:23:17.85,0:23:25.83,Song,,0,0,0,,Amid the people’s cheering cries\Nnow march forth from the land of their fathers and mothers
Dialogue: 10,0:23:25.83,0:23:33.53,Song,,0,0,0,,Sworn that if we do not win, alive we shall not return—\NHow valiant is the heart that swears it!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.32,0:23:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, two o'clock. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.25,0:23:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.89,0:23:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.84,0:24:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already awake, sir?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.93,0:24:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The blockade squad should be \Nreaching Port Arthur about now. {this is admiral togo}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:35.40,0:24:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Commander Hirose's report have a liason? {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hirose_Takeo}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:37.83,0:24:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:38.83,0:24:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Full speed.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:39.93,0:24:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Full speed!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:46.29,0:24:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy sighted. \NApproaching the designated position. Full speed! {this shit is absolutely impenetrable to me, believing the script mostly, but often even that fails in battle scenes like this so I'm just making something plausible up and you can't judge me }
Dialogue: 10,0:24:49.64,0:24:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire! Full speed ahead!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:51.78,0:24:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger! Full speed ahead!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:04.00,0:25:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop anchor! {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:04.99,0:25:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop anchor!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:06.23,0:25:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare the charges!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.40,0:25:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare the charges!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:26.85,0:25:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first attempt to blockade Port Arthur's Harbor was confused by the enemy's sharp maneuvers,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:31.95,0:25:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were unable to achieve the expected results.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:34.82,0:25:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously, ships could pass the harbor in thirty minutes, \Nbut after the blockade, it now takes two hours.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:40.59,0:25:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In wartime, a difference of an hour and a half \Nmeans enormous losses for the enemy.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:44.83,0:25:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore we will dispatch a second blockade squad, \Nand I wished to discuss the selection of its members.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:51.04,0:25:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief of Staff. When you speak of selecting men \Nfor the second attempt, do you mean to replace us?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:56.21,0:25:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Miraculously, you, the pride of the Navy, returned alive.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:59.18,0:26:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, you will return to your ship Asahi and rest.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:01.98,0:26:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This time I will select from among two thousand volunteers.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:05.39,0:26:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Colonels Yamada, Oe, and Inoue \Nwill take part as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:09.46,0:26:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying, Chief of Staff?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:12.30,0:26:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If this measure is out of concern for my life, \NI must protest.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:16.48,0:26:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are Lieutenant Colonel Arima \Nand Commander Hirose not to be assigned this noble duty?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:22.88,0:26:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, Hirose didn't expect to return alive from the first blockade mission.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:31.24,0:26:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,During the first blockade, \Na transport ships rushed forward,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:34.38,0:26:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that, among other accidents, will serve as valuable lessons \Nfor the second blockade.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:39.69,0:26:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Colonel Arima and Major Hirose posess such experience.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:43.16,0:26:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you came, I requested this, \Nbut permission was not granted.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:47.19,0:26:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:48.94,0:26:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Please assign us to the mission.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.53,0:26:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Major Hirose.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:52.77,0:26:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of two thousand volunteers, if you commanded the second blockade unit too, what of the men?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.17,0:27:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the seventy sailors be the ones who served the first mission?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:00.31,0:27:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you not understand Admiral Togo's intentions?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:02.11,0:27:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:02.78,0:27:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, silence?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:03.84,0:27:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have you arrested! {???? 参謀稽首を取れ。}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:04.55,0:27:05.65,Overlap,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:04.81,0:27:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, wait, wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:05.98,0:27:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are so close \Nyou fight like brothers. {lit: you're too close, so when you argue, it's impossible to get you to stop - meaning that if there less close, they wouldn't be so adamant about showing one another up}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.18,0:27:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief of Staff, even so, I am the commanding officer.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:10.75,0:27:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree that the men should be newly selected,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:14.43,0:27:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but I object to replacing the commander.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:17.89,0:27:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:19.34,0:27:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Colonel Arima and Major Hirose.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:21.77,0:27:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of the nation, \NI ask you to carry out this mission once again.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:30.15,0:27:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Commanders Arima and Hirose, \NI am counting on you.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:34.54,0:27:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We swear we will succeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:43.16,0:27:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Second blockade unit—banzai! {meaning that they're cheering on the second unit}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:45.90,0:27:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:09.32,0:28:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Shikido, are preparations complete?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.44,0:28:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're entering the harbor.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:12.65,0:28:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Five hundred to the designated position.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:14.65,0:28:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope no torpedoes come before then.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:32.41,0:28:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Two hundred to go.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:33.90,0:28:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare the charges!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:35.23,0:28:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare the charges!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:36.44,0:28:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare the charges!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:44.69,0:28:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it, we've been hit by a torpedo!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:58.17,0:29:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All hands abandon ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:00.03,0:29:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All hands abandon ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:08.44,0:29:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Shikido! Shikido!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:20.39,0:29:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Shikido!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:22.69,0:29:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Shikido here? \NWhere is Shikido?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:26.55,0:29:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, it's dangerous! Please evacuate!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:28.43,0:29:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry, get to the lifeboat!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:30.54,0:29:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Shikido!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:42.35,0:29:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Shikido!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:43.57,0:29:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The blockade was a success!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:47.05,0:29:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a fine soldier!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:50.52,0:29:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Shikido!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:56.76,0:29:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, quickly get to the lifeboats!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:59.36,0:30:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander! It's dangerous! \NHurry, get on the boat!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:08.41,0:30:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:18.25,0:30:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, in the two attempts to blockade Port Arthur Harbor, \Nresults exceeding all expectations were achieved.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:24.74,0:30:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like last time, the courageous and calm leadership of Naval Major Hirose Takeo,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:30.48,0:30:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and his deep concern for his men was truly the essence \Nof a warrior's spirit, a shining example for all commanders.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:36.72,0:30:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the major's remains, only fragments of flesh \Nand a sea chart stained with blood were recovered.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:43.24,0:30:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Send a messenger
Dialogue: 10,0:30:46.07,0:30:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,at once to Hirose's family.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:48.95,0:30:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir. Your gracious words \Nwill surely raise the morale of the entire navy.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:58.81,0:31:29.81,Song,,0,0,0,,The greatness of the Yamato spirit of our land of Shikishima reveals itself in times of trial {trusting chatgpt}
Dialogue: 10,0:31:31.69,0:31:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Time passes quickly.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:33.48,0:31:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already been nearly two months \Nsince Lieutenant Colonel Hirose fell in battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:38.36,0:31:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:39.02,0:31:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Akiyama? \NYou look pale.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:40.89,0:31:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoshino and Kasuga have collided. {https://www.lookandlearn.com/history-images/M694154/Ramming-of-the-Japanese-cruiser-Yoshino-1904}
Dialogue: 10,0:31:43.02,0:31:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Collided?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:44.19,0:31:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:46.08,0:31:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Commander Dewa's report,
Dialogue: 10,0:31:48.33,0:31:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1:40 a.m. on May 15 the Third Squadron encountered heavy fog while engaged in the blockade of Port Arthur,
Dialogue: 10,0:31:54.43,0:31:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,causing the Kasuga to strike the Yoshino's port side.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:57.00,0:31:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yoshino took on heavy water and sank.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:00.74,0:32:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is truly a terrible matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:04.72,0:32:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Investigate the details and report \Nto Imperial Headquarters at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:09.08,0:32:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, in our report to Imperial Headquarters, \Nwe must submit a request to resign.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:15.09,0:32:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You think resigning from your post \Nwill free you from responsibility?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:18.42,0:32:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:19.39,0:32:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is wartime.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:22.56,0:32:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Until disciplinary action is decided, I cannot resign.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:31.62,0:32:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, a grave matter has occurred.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:33.57,0:32:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this about Yoshino and Kasuga colliding?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:36.13,0:32:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:37.28,0:32:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatsuse and Yashima have struck enemy mines and sunk. {https://20thcenturywars.com/may-15-1904-two-japanese-battleships-hatsuse-and-yashima-sink-after-hitting-mines-laid-by-the-russian-minelayer-amur/}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:41.79,0:32:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Battleship Hatsuse has been lost?!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:43.48,0:32:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:44.68,0:32:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Are you certain there's no mistake?!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:02.67,0:33:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time we have lost four vessels—\Nbattleships and cruisers—and it pains me deeply to report it.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:12.42,0:33:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It is war.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:15.29,0:33:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One might even say all the naval battles \Nuntil now have been fortunate for us.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:21.13,0:33:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You must not lose heart over such matters.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:25.20,0:33:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:26.49,0:33:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, what of the men? \NWere they rescued?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:31.13,0:33:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Read the report.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:32.43,0:33:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:37.75,0:33:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All hands prepare to abandon ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:40.67,0:33:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All hands prepare to abandon ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:43.09,0:33:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to abandon ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:49.36,0:33:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain and executive officer \Nordered the men to the boats first.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:54.15,0:33:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Saeki, Executive Officer Hirose, \Nand Navigator Takeda
Dialogue: 10,0:33:58.26,0:34:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,remained behind after sending the men to the boats, \Nand calmly offered their apologies to His Majesty,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:04.70,0:34:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,shouting “Long live the Emperor! Long live the Empire!” \Nbefore sharing the fate of their ship.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:11.74,0:34:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When the rescue teams rushed to the scene,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:16.68,0:34:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the sailors thrown into the sea, without regard for their own danger, \Nfirst pleaded for their officers to be saved,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:24.75,0:34:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,while the officers ordered them to save the men instead. \NThus the true spirit of Bushido...
Dialogue: 10,0:34:30.70,0:34:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,before our very eyes...
Dialogue: 10,0:34:33.34,0:34:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,blossomed beautifully!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:36.88,0:34:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It is most regrettable \Nthat several ships were lost at once
Dialogue: 10,0:34:41.20,0:34:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and that so many of His Majesty's \Nloyal officers and men were sacrificed.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:45.87,0:34:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I am filled with deep shame.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:48.99,0:34:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I humbly request that I be relieved of my post.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:02.90,0:35:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I share the same feelings as the Chief of the Naval Staff.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:10.71,0:35:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Togo made the same request?
Dialogue: 10,0:35:21.39,0:35:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not believe he has!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:24.56,0:35:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ito and Yamamoto may resign \Nand thus escape all responsibility,
Dialogue: 10,0:35:34.00,0:35:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but the Emperor has no such option.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:36.49,0:35:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:46.68,0:35:49.87,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the army had already secured order in Korea
Dialogue: 10,0:35:49.87,0:35:55.64,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,and opened a vast battlefront across the plains of southern Manchuria with an army of one hundred thousand.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:55.64,0:35:59.61,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,General Kuroki's First Army, \NOku's Second Army, and Nozu's Fourth Army
Dialogue: 10,0:35:59.61,0:36:04.98,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,pressed forward like a splitting bamboo toward Liaoyang, \Nthe site of the enemy's headquarters. {(with) great vigour (from the way splitting bamboo goes all down the stick); irresistible force​ - if this sounds too abstract, just go with "like an unstoppable force" or something}
Dialogue: 10,0:36:11.86,0:36:15.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, General Nogi, \Ncommander of the Third Army,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:15.03,0:36:20.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,visited the headquarters of Marshal Oyama, commander-in-chief of the Manchurian Army, alongside Chief of Staff Kodama,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:20.83,0:36:23.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to discuss operations against Port Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:26.15,0:36:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:32.55,0:36:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Port Arthur is defended by thirty thousand Russian troops and six hundred guns,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:36.58,0:36:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,with sixty heavily fortified artillery batteries confirmed.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:39.62,0:36:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Its scale is almost without equal in the world.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:42.72,0:36:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the timing of the general assault, unless the navy first restrains the Vladivostok fleet and the Port Arthur fleet to some extent,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:49.36,0:36:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,our army's casualties will be extremely heavy.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:51.85,0:36:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Eastern Railway from Mukden to Dalian has already been destroyed, so the enemy's supply line has been cut in half.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:58.37,0:36:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:59.27,0:37:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,General Stessel boasts that Port Arthur, \Neven without further supplies,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:02.64,0:37:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,could hold out for two years against the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:05.11,0:37:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But during the Sino-Japanese War, \Ndidn’t Port Arthur fall in two days?
Dialogue: 10,0:37:08.45,0:37:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The outer defensive positions of Port Arthur—\NMount Takushan and Xiaokushan— {I'm not finding those on the map but I also have no clue what they originally might've been or even where to start looking}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:11.98,0:37:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,should, I believe, be captured by August 10.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:14.29,0:37:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can capture them by then, \Nit will be a great success.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:17.06,0:37:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Could Port Arthur, riding this momentum, \Nalso be taken by October?
Dialogue: 10,0:37:20.43,0:37:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Port Arthur is on an entirely different scale \Nfrom Nanshan or Flanders. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Nanshan / no idea what that other word could be, flanden? flanberg? I'm not finding anything of sorts around dalian or any battle earlier in the war, and chatgpt is just convincing me he is comparing it to european warfare or something, using "flanders" as a collective noun...}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:24.18,0:37:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of Nanshan, \NI heard the commander's son was killed there. {referring to the guy sitting in front of them}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:28.87,0:37:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Reports say he distinguished himself.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:31.65,0:37:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To have found a place to die in battle—\NKatsusuke met an honorable end. {not finding any info about that}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:35.94,0:37:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The commander has not yet visited \Nthe place where his son fell.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:45.56,0:37:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Staff Officer Iguchi, take him there at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:47.82,0:37:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that won't be necessary.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:50.36,0:37:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We will pass Nanshan on the way back.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:55.41,0:38:02.37,Song,,0,0,0,,Mountains and rivers, grasses and trees
Dialogue: 10,0:38:02.37,0:38:10.61,Song,,0,0,0,,I shall shape into song
Dialogue: 10,0:38:10.61,0:38:24.89,Song,,0,0,0,,Ten miles of wind carry the stench of the new battlefield
Dialogue: 10,0:38:24.89,0:38:38.64,Song,,0,0,0,,The warhorse advances in silence, no man speaking
Dialogue: 10,0:38:38.64,0:38:55.37,Song,,0,0,0,,Outside the walls of Kinzhou, I stand in the slanting evening sun
Dialogue: 10,0:38:55.37,0:38:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:38:58.74,0:39:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Extra! Extra! Read the news!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:02.03,0:39:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Extra! Extra!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:04.61,0:39:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{more of the same}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:15.22,0:39:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,With our victory at the Battle of the Yellow Sea, \Nit has been decided to begin the general assault on Port Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:21.91,0:39:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear that there are many noncombatants \Ninside the fortress at Port Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:26.93,0:39:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:28.53,0:39:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said there are a considerable number \Nof women and children as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:32.32,0:39:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Inform them so that noncombatants \Nmay be spared from the flames of war. {inform them of the assault I guess?}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:38.41,0:39:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We humbly obey Your Majesty's will.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:03.27,0:40:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Staff Officer Yamaoka.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:04.22,0:40:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:05.09,0:40:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Convey His Majesty's wishes, and issue \Nrepeated proclamations urging the evacuation of women,
Dialogue: 10,0:40:09.50,0:40:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,children, and other noncombatants \Nfrom the Port Arthur fortress.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:13.40,0:40:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:17.68,0:40:20.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On August 16, Staff Officer Yamaoka
Dialogue: 10,0:40:20.77,0:40:26.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,delivered a message along the entire Port Arthur front calling on the Russian army to surrender
Dialogue: 10,0:40:26.01,0:40:34.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and urging the evacuation of noncombatants, \Nbut Stessel refused, and the Third Army resolved to proceed.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:00.09,0:41:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:13.74,0:41:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Halt!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:32.54,0:41:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:33.41,0:41:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Go on, hurry forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:30.44,0:42:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Move out!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:43.29,0:42:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Excellency, the enemy's resistance is far stronger than expected.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:47.15,0:42:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This will not be easy.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:48.99,0:42:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief of Staff.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:51.00,0:42:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is using new weapons.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:53.39,0:42:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Those machine guns we had heard about?
Dialogue: 10,0:42:55.56,0:42:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:56.33,0:42:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of them, our casualties are mounting terribly.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:59.26,0:43:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Launch night attacks, push cautiously, \Nand secure the present position.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:02.10,0:43:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:18.35,0:43:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire! Go! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:43:31.40,0:43:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:43:32.27,0:43:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 10,0:43:45.29,0:43:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Excellency, the battle will be prolonged. \NPerhaps you should take some rest.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:51.50,0:43:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A report has come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:52.62,0:43:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:53.29,0:43:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The right wing of the First Horie assault force has been wiped out.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:56.46,0:43:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wiped out?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:57.42,0:43:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:55.59,0:44:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hang in there!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:56.93,0:44:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:44:57.52,0:44:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay with us!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:01.13,0:45:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring it up quickly!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:31.35,0:45:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Russians are using new weapons, like machine guns and electrified barbed wire,
Dialogue: 10,0:45:35.19,0:45:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so our army's attacks are meeting extreme difficulty.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:37.72,0:45:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that these new weapons are being used for the first time \Nshows just how important the enemy considers this fortress.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:43.66,0:45:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A frontal assault seems entirely impossible.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:47.00,0:45:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,At present we cannot even retrieve the wounded.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:50.87,0:45:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the greatest fortress in the world, \Nbuilt with all the enemy's strength.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:54.34,0:45:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The operational plan must be revised from the ground up.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:56.81,0:45:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Revised from the ground up?
Dialogue: 10,0:45:58.38,0:46:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a vast difference between the weapons \Nour army uses and those of the Russians!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:02.21,0:46:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 10,0:46:03.38,0:46:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Imperial Headquarters has given strict orders that, \Nby any means necessary,
Dialogue: 10,0:46:07.32,0:46:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Port Arthur must be taken \Nbefore the Baltic Fleet reaches the Sea of Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:15.41,0:46:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay with us!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:22.98,0:46:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't die! Don't you die!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:26.94,0:46:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:46:29.59,0:46:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:39.13,0:46:41.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After four days of fierce fighting,
Dialogue: 10,0:46:42.10,0:46:45.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the general assault ended in failure,
Dialogue: 10,0:46:45.36,0:46:49.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and our army suffered more than fifteen thousand casualties.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:08.36,0:47:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever His Majesty's official duties allow him time, \Nhe examines the casualty lists and asks many questions.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:14.15,0:47:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the fallen, even down to the ordinary soldiers?
Dialogue: 10,0:47:16.45,0:47:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:17.46,0:47:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At times His Majesty remarks that in this battle many named Kato died, or in another battle many named Yamada,
Dialogue: 10,0:47:22.46,0:47:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and from this we can sense the depth of his concern.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:25.43,0:47:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat like this could harm His Majesty's health.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:28.07,0:47:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet he wears his winter uniform.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:29.97,0:47:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What? That's his winter uniform?
Dialogue: 10,0:47:32.54,0:47:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He has not permitted it to be changed.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:35.39,0:47:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,While attending to affairs of state, \Nhe wishes always to be as one with the soldiers.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:39.71,0:47:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks you very much for waiting.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:54.03,0:47:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In this intense heat, seeing Your Majesty \Ncontinuing your labors fills us with awe.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:59.06,0:48:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This summer seems especially hot.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:03.20,0:48:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Your Majesty, today I bring news \Nthat may make you forget the heat.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:08.81,0:48:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:48:10.18,0:48:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the intense efforts \Nof Takahashi Korekiyo in America,
Dialogue: 10,0:48:13.45,0:48:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,following the success of the first \Nforeign loan of ten million pounds,
Dialogue: 10,0:48:17.32,0:48:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the second loan of twelve million pounds \Nhas also been approved by Britain and America.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:24.09,0:48:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? That is excellent news.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:27.94,0:48:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Takahashi must have worked very hard indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:30.56,0:48:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:31.56,0:48:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have also received word that the outlook \Nfor further foreign loans is very promising.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:38.87,0:48:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the people know that Britain, America, \Nand the other nations have come to understand Japan's position.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:49.03,0:48:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:51.25,0:48:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Your Majesty, about your poem, "Though all the seas in every direction are thought to be born of one kin, {13:10}
Dialogue: 10,0:48:58.22,0:49:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,why do the winds and waves \Nrise and rage against one another?"
Dialogue: 10,0:49:00.99,0:49:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When Takahashi showed its English translation to President Roosevelt of the United States,
Dialogue: 10,0:49:06.87,0:49:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the president was deeply moved \Nby the greatness and compassion of Your Majesty's heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:20.69,0:49:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:22.83,0:49:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the war began, Your Majesty has not rested a single day,
Dialogue: 10,0:49:26.55,0:49:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,nor have you once visited \Nthe imperial villas or summer residences.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:30.79,0:49:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In this intense heat, might it not be wise \Nto spend a short time at a cooler retreat?
Dialogue: 10,0:49:39.40,0:49:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ito.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:40.20,0:49:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:42.07,0:49:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the soldiers at the front enjoy a summer retreat?
Dialogue: 10,0:49:49.15,0:50:13.13,Song,,0,0,0,,The warriors, how do they endure the heat, even longing for water, in such a place?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:13.13,0:50:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{Heave-ho, heave-ho!}
Dialogue: 10,0:50:17.41,0:50:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't drink it! Stop! \NDon't drink that muddy water!
Dialogue: 10,0:50:21.24,0:50:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold yourself together.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:22.47,0:50:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Once Liaoyang falls, there will be water.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:25.14,0:50:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, just a little longer! \NGet it together!
Dialogue: 10,0:50:28.25,0:50:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't waste the lives of the infantry on the front line! {by taking longer than needed ig}
Dialogue: 10,0:50:30.92,0:50:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:37.00,0:50:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:37.94,0:50:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:42.24,0:50:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:45.44,0:50:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:51.75,0:51:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Tachibana Battalion will launch the general assault \Non Liaoyang tomorrow at four in the morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:02.01,0:51:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The target of our regiment's attack, Shoushanpu Fort, \Nis expected to see the fiercest fighting next to Port Arthur!
Dialogue: 10,0:51:11.06,0:51:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect every single soldier \Nto charge into Shoushanpu Fort's trenches!
Dialogue: 10,0:51:16.26,0:51:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That is all.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:22.95,0:51:26.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At dawn on August 31,
Dialogue: 10,0:51:26.24,0:51:34.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the attack on Liaoyang was opened by the elite troops of the Third Division under Lieutenant General Oshima.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:34.15,0:51:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A report!
Dialogue: 10,0:51:35.78,0:51:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The assault on Shoushanpu Fort is extremely fierce.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:38.05,0:51:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The 34th Shizuoka Regiment has advanced within five hundred meters
Dialogue: 10,0:51:41.42,0:51:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and is now engaged in hand-to-hand combat.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:47.69,0:51:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:00.48,0:52:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:20.30,0:52:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:31.75,0:52:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:34.20,0:52:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you... follow Major Tachibana!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:37.08,0:52:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:47.80,0:52:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the nearby position secured? {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:52:49.15,0:52:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the position is secured.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:50.82,0:52:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:55.66,0:53:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{???? that supposed to be russian? I can only hear "davai" = come on }
Dialogue: 10,0:53:10.69,0:53:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:15.18,0:53:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:17.12,0:53:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me. Just get out of here!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:19.65,0:53:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:27.83,0:53:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Take command and lead them out!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:29.79,0:53:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:31.23,0:53:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Please hand over command!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:33.53,0:53:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:35.10,0:53:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Lieutenant Nakayoshi, \Nlead the unit across the line!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:39.60,0:53:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:41.24,0:53:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{??? kinda sounds like "Vperyod" = "ahead/forward"}
Dialogue: 10,0:53:47.91,0:53:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:51.12,0:53:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:54.33,0:53:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:55.50,0:53:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Please hold on!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:09.28,0:54:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander, stay with us!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:16.05,0:54:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Corporal, what's the situation? {??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:54:20.09,0:54:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It has fallen.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:22.13,0:54:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoushanpu Fort has fallen!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:27.35,0:54:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's fallen...
Dialogue: 10,0:54:29.22,0:54:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Our regimental colors? {battle flag; standard; (regimental) colours; colors; ensign}
Dialogue: 10,0:54:30.29,0:54:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Lieutenant Nagayama has them!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:33.02,0:54:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please use this and evacuate! {??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:54:36.47,0:54:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,East... head east!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:40.58,0:54:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:43.91,0:54:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is August 31st, isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:54:46.80,0:54:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:48.72,0:54:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The birthday of His Imperial Highness \Nthe Crown Prince, whom we serve.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:54.48,0:54:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:58.23,0:55:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:55:05.60,0:55:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The day before yesterday, on His Imperial Highness \Nthe Crown Prince's birthday, Shoushanpu Fort fell.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:10.03,0:55:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems the fall of Liaoyang is now close at hand.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:13.26,0:55:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish to commend the regiment that distinguished itself \Nin the capture of Shoushanpu Fort.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:19.82,0:55:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the 34th Shizuoka Regiment.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:21.91,0:55:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In that battle, Regimental Commander Colonel Sekiya,
Dialogue: 10,0:55:24.31,0:55:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion Commander Major Tachibana, and nearly all the officers were killed, and the regiment was annihilated.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:29.68,0:55:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Tachibana?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:32.26,0:55:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That Major Tachibana who once served under Togo?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:36.82,0:55:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To remember his name \Nthrough all these years—remarkable.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:39.66,0:55:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tachibana himself surely died fulfilled.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:43.33,0:55:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When Tachibana's right hand was shot by the enemy \Nand he switched his sword to his left,
Dialogue: 10,0:55:48.40,0:55:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he was struck again in the left hand by a bullet, \Nyet he fought on like a demon incarnate,
Dialogue: 10,0:55:53.64,0:55:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,shouting that since today was the Crown Prince's birthday, \Nthere must be no retreat,
Dialogue: 10,0:55:59.08,0:56:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,until he was hit in the chest by another bullet.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:01.75,0:56:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding aloft the case of the regimental colors, \Nhe offered congratulations for the Crown Prince's birthday,
Dialogue: 10,0:56:07.47,0:56:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and while calling out “Long live His Majesty,” \Nhe met an honorable death in battle—that is the report.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:13.67,0:56:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure Admiral Togo is informed of this in full.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:24.55,0:56:31.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Russian Navy's greatest force, the Baltic Fleet, set out \Nto reclaim command of the seas in the Far East in a single stroke.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:31.78,0:56:36.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On October 19th it departed its home port \Nof Libau and headed for the Orient. {"Finally, on 10 October 1904, he reviewed the armada at the port of Reval [present-day Tallinn, Estonia]. The next day the force of 42 warships and 12,000 officers and sailors left for Libau [Libava, present-day Liepaja in Latvia], and after coaling it departed on 15 October for a voyage of 33,000 kilometers [18,000 nautical miles] to an unknown destiny." - actually could be either Libau or Reval lol}
Dialogue: 10,0:56:37.63,0:56:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though the Baltic Fleet has now sailed, \Nnot a single key fortress at Port Arthur has fallen.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:42.89,0:56:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been two months since the general assault began, \Nwhat in the world is our army doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:47.39,0:56:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Togo has gone to see \NGeneral Nogi about that very matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:51.06,0:56:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Best not to raise too much of a commotion.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:53.42,0:56:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Baltic Fleet is expected to appear \Nnear Japanese waters no later than late January.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:57.84,0:57:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If Hill 203 can be taken before then, the enemy ships inside Port Arthur harbor can be completely destroyed. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hill_203}
Dialogue: 10,0:57:03.07,0:57:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Chief of Staff Shimamura believes so, \Nso it is hardly surprising
Dialogue: 10,0:57:07.38,0:57:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that the government and the people are asking \Nwhat is being done after sacrificing twenty thousand men.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:12.17,0:57:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if Port Arthur does not fall by December, \Nthe navy will have to lift the blockade of the harbor
Dialogue: 10,0:57:17.86,0:57:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to meet the Baltic Fleet,\Nas we simply do not have enough ships!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:21.29,0:57:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be a problem. If that happens, the dozen or so \Nenemy ships pinned deep inside Port Arthur harbor
Dialogue: 10,0:57:26.26,0:57:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,would begin appearing in Japanese coastal waters and on the high seas, threatening our supply lines!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:32.45,0:57:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If it does not fall by December, then the navy will have to take that extremely risky gamble! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:57:36.57,0:57:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All the effort up to now would be wasted!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:38.44,0:57:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:39.94,0:57:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what sacrifices must be made, \Neven if we build mountains of the dead,
Dialogue: 10,0:57:44.49,0:57:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Port Arthur must fall within December \Nto secure the safety of the nation.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:52.44,0:57:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the people's resentment, \NI alone, Nogi, will bear it.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:57.50,0:57:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Excellency.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:59.50,0:58:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the harsh fate of war, so many precious lives \Nmust be sacrificed to break the enemy's defenses.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:07.57,0:58:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, a commander's heart must surely find that unbearable.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:19.83,0:58:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet no matter how we press or attack, the enemy will not budge, \Nand now the eyes of the entire world are fixed upon Port Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:27.19,0:58:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When I think of the sons, fathers, and brothers \Nwho have died such heroic deaths at Port Arthur,
Dialogue: 10,0:58:33.28,0:58:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I realize how merciless war truly is.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:36.00,0:58:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we do not overcome it, \Neven greater tragedy will come to Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:41.71,0:58:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Vladivostok squadron once escaped,
Dialogue: 10,0:58:44.38,0:58:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there was the disgraceful incident of the public \Nstorming the homes of Admirals Kamimura and Uriu!
Dialogue: 10,0:58:50.22,0:58:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that the Baltic Fleet\N is at last heading toward the East,
Dialogue: 10,0:58:55.59,0:59:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,if voices among the people begin asking \Nwhat the army attacking Port Arthur is doing,
Dialogue: 10,0:59:02.39,0:59:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then that would mean we have fallen \Ninto the enemy's plan to disturb our rear!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:08.03,0:59:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I propose that today's public meeting \Non the Port Arthur attack become a rally to encourage the Third Army,
Dialogue: 10,0:59:16.01,0:59:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the people, united as one, \Nmay of their own will support the home front!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:24.66,0:59:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{???? maybe "a word" or "silence"}
Dialogue: 10,0:59:27.22,0:59:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,My son died in the fighting at Port Arthur!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:31.74,0:59:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But I hear that General Nogi's eldest son \Nhas also been killed in action.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:36.86,0:59:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing more to say!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:40.03,0:59:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We, the bereaved families, insist that Port Arthur be taken!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:49.09,0:59:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Sugimoto has brought up a matter \Nregarding your son, Second Lieutenant Nogi.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:54.01,0:59:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Yasusuke done something wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:59:56.95,1:00:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was suggested that he step down from leading \Na front-line platoon and be assigned to headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:01.12,1:00:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Since your eldest son, Lieutenant Katsusuke, \Nhas already fallen.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:05.19,1:00:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That won't be necessary.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:06.36,1:00:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But Your Excellency!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:07.53,1:00:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not pull Yasusuke back from the front.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:11.24,1:00:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,To do so would be unfair \Nto the many officers and men who have already died.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:16.28,1:00:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,According to today's foreign dispatch, \Nthe Baltic Fleet has passed the coasts of Spain and Portugal.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:21.07,1:00:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Baltic Fleet reaches Japanese waters before Port Arthur falls, it will be a grave situation.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:26.14,1:00:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The war situation would likely \Nturn completely against us.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:29.28,1:00:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Port Arthur must be taken as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:31.58,1:00:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Port Arthur is truly impregnable.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:34.89,1:00:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Togo met with Commander Nogi the other day, \Nbut they have yet to reach a conclusion.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:39.42,1:00:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Does the army have no prospect \Nof taking Port Arthur within December?
Dialogue: 10,1:00:43.29,1:00:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering all the circumstances, \NI fear even by the end of January it may prove impossible.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:47.73,1:00:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Before this desperate struggle, \Nperhaps General Nogi's command should be replaced? {and new leadership appointed}
Dialogue: 10,1:00:52.07,1:00:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,1:00:52.92,1:00:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We in the navy want Port Arthur to fall as soon as possible, \Neven if it means replacing the commander.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:57.11,1:01:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If the general assaults up to now have been failures, \Nthen replacing the commander may be unavoidable!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:02.06,1:01:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But that would be tantamount \Nto forcing General Nogi to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:05.40,1:01:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, we cannot let sentiment guide us.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:08.42,1:01:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 10,1:01:10.92,1:01:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The voices saying General Nogi \Nis unfit are growing very strong.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:13.62,1:01:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Even some within the army are saying the same.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:16.09,1:01:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a disgrace at a most critical time!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:18.30,1:01:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, we earnestly beg for your decisive judgment!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:21.67,1:01:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, since this matter is so grave, \Nperhaps you should report it directly to His Majesty.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:30.35,1:01:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Orderly, bring another meal.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:33.38,1:01:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:34.25,1:01:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No, never mind.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:35.51,1:01:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, I have one with me.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:38.12,1:01:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,1:01:39.45,1:01:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:45.27,1:01:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,His Majesty is at his meal just now, \Nbut he says it does not matter.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:48.53,1:01:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm, but when he's done eating...
Dialogue: 10,1:01:50.73,1:01:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No, when His Majesty says it does not matter, \Nthat means you can see him at once. {I don't know what's the point of this funny exchange but it seems to be what they're saying}
Dialogue: 10,1:02:06.56,1:02:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, do you always eat the same food as the soldiers?
Dialogue: 10,1:02:10.56,1:02:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:11.68,1:02:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That lets me remain here at home like this.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:26.24,1:02:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,1:02:36.82,1:02:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I do not know when I may see you again, \NI would like to have a photograph taken with you today.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:43.68,1:02:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{okay}
Dialogue: 10,1:02:47.06,1:02:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Your regiment is to move around the flank \Nof Hill 203, is it not?
Dialogue: 10,1:02:51.69,1:02:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:55.47,1:02:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This was my brother's keepsake \Nafter he fell in battle. I leave it in your care.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:02.11,1:03:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:03.60,1:03:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Your resolve is admirable.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:08.62,1:03:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell your mother about it.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:13.72,1:03:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:15.51,1:03:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It must weigh on your heart \Nto have sent tens of thousands of men to their deaths...
Dialogue: 10,1:03:21.55,1:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yasusuke!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:22.72,1:03:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,1:03:24.39,1:03:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself wish to go to the front,
Dialogue: 10,1:03:28.67,1:03:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to die in battle alongside the officers and men.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:34.63,1:03:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We humbly ask for Your Majesty's judgment in this matter.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:38.34,1:03:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nogi must not be replaced!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:46.34,1:03:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no one but Nogi who can take Port Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:50.62,1:03:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you replace Nogi now,
Dialogue: 10,1:03:53.33,1:03:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the one who will rejoice most \Nis the enemy commander, Stessel.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:58.92,1:04:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nogi will surely take Port Arthur before long!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:04.56,1:04:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty's will shall be engraved upon my heart.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:08.67,1:04:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My shallow thinking is inexcusable.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:13.18,1:04:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is enough that you understand.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:17.02,1:04:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I desire full cooperation between the army and navy.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:31.69,1:04:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Excellency, how did it go?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:38.24,1:04:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,By His Majesty's will, \Nthe dismissal of Commander Nogi has been withdrawn.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:43.77,1:04:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again I was humbled by His Majesty's greatness \Nand by the keen eye with which he judges men.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:53.86,1:04:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Aide-de-Camp. {武官長。}
Dialogue: 10,1:04:54.75,1:04:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:55.41,1:04:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything special about today?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:56.75,1:04:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing unusual, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:58.18,1:05:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we happened to see His Majesty's meal... {probably some comment about how emperor's meal was also humble and soldier-like}
Dialogue: 10,1:05:00.62,1:05:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he eats that every other day without fail.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:04.05,1:05:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That naval ration?
Dialogue: 10,1:05:05.96,1:05:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how we beg him to stop, he will not permit it.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:12.88,1:05:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmit His Majesty's message to the Third Army.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:23.15,1:05:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in the present circumstances \Nthe situation of the army and navy alike
Dialogue: 10,1:05:28.41,1:05:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,does not permit delay in the capture of Port Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:33.45,1:05:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At this moment,
Dialogue: 10,1:05:34.74,1:05:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing that the Third Army \Nhas been granted permission for a general assault,
Dialogue: 10,1:05:38.82,1:05:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I rejoice greatly and earnestly hope for its success.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:45.54,1:05:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,On this third day of November, we have unexpectedly received this most gracious message,
Dialogue: 10,1:05:51.70,1:05:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and with this inspiration our officers and men shall unite as one \Nto carry out the general assault on Port Arthur
Dialogue: 10,1:05:58.34,1:06:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and thus answer His Majesty's will.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:02.46,1:06:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Facing toward the distant Imperial Palace, \Nwe celebrate this auspicious day {literally, the turn towards tokyo}
Dialogue: 10,1:06:07.45,1:06:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and offer three cheers for His Majesty's long life. {= banzai}
Dialogue: 10,1:06:15.34,1:06:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the Emperor!
Dialogue: 10,1:06:20.00,1:06:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,1:06:49.26,1:06:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear the voices of the people.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:52.34,1:06:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okazawa, I can hear the voices of the people.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:59.28,1:07:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly the Imperial banner. {Imperial Standard}
Dialogue: 10,1:07:01.05,1:07:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:11.57,1:07:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{Banzai!}
Dialogue: 10,1:07:31.08,1:07:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{Banzai!}
Dialogue: 10,1:07:49.77,1:08:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hill 203, a corner of the Port Arthur fortress, has already seen countless of our soldiers fall in bitter defeat.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:00.45,1:08:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The success or failure of this third general assault
Dialogue: 10,1:08:05.34,1:08:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,will determine the fate of the nation.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:08.78,1:08:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, with the spirit of giving your life \Nfor the country, carry out the attack.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:16.30,1:08:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We all swear to fulfill our duty.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:21.46,1:08:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us give three farewell cheers to our homeland. {parting banzai}
Dialogue: 10,1:08:28.39,1:08:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The assault unit will, at 6:00 a.m., \Nattempt to seize the flat ground at the flank of Hill 203.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:35.71,1:08:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Nogi platoon, according to orders, \Nwill crawl forward to the assault position by 5:00 a.m.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:43.69,1:08:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No firing is permitted until arrival.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:12.34,1:09:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawn has broken.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:13.60,1:09:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nogi, you have not rested?
Dialogue: 10,1:09:16.44,1:09:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Has there been any report from the front?
Dialogue: 10,1:09:25.93,1:09:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:28.60,1:09:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:09:31.93,1:09:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:09:37.47,1:09:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:10:09.04,1:10:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Advance in order!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:20.97,1:10:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Get them! {???}
Dialogue: 10,1:10:29.86,1:10:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hang on!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:31.13,1:10:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:10:32.28,1:10:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Platoon leader! {???}
Dialogue: 10,1:10:36.52,1:10:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave me and go!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:39.07,1:10:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Platoon leader!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:43.83,1:10:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Platoon leader!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:45.00,1:10:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:47.04,1:10:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:10:49.00,1:10:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Platoon leader!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:53.07,1:10:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Advance!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:56.14,1:10:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Platoon leader!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:57.78,1:11:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone... hold the line!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:01.78,1:11:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:05.79,1:11:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:13.66,1:11:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:11:16.16,1:11:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{???}
Dialogue: 10,1:11:19.50,1:11:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:29.72,1:11:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NStill no contact?
Dialogue: 10,1:11:31.84,1:11:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! At 8:00 a.m., the Fujimoto Regiment \Nsucceeded in capturing Hill 203.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:36.16,1:11:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They captured it?
Dialogue: 10,1:11:37.15,1:11:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But no supporting units followed, \Nso the details are still unclear.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:40.22,1:11:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even reaching Hill 203 is a success.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:43.50,1:11:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Before long, we will surely have taken it.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:50.66,1:11:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant, according to the report of a soldier \Nthrown down from the summit...
Dialogue: 10,1:11:54.70,1:12:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Brigade Commander Nakamura and many others \Nare confirmed to have died heroic deaths in battle!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:02.28,1:12:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all the report says?
Dialogue: 10,1:12:05.05,1:12:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It also says Your Excellency's son met a glorious end.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:40.12,1:12:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nogi...
Dialogue: 10,1:12:43.58,1:12:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:46.20,1:12:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,At least now I can offer some apology \Nto the bereaved families.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:52.20,1:12:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He died well.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:56.94,1:13:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Excellency, \NHill 203 will surely fall within the month.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:04.51,1:13:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I say this as a final tribute to your son.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:10.29,1:13:20.65,Song,,0,0,0,,Though steep stands Hill 203,
Dialogue: 10,1:13:20.65,1:13:30.37,Song,,0,0,0,,who says it cannot be climbed?
Dialogue: 10,1:13:30.37,1:13:39.20,Song,,0,0,0,,A man's glory
Dialogue: 10,1:13:39.20,1:13:47.18,Song,,0,0,0,,lies in overcoming hardship
Dialogue: 10,1:13:47.18,1:14:09.34,Song,,0,0,0,,Iron and blood cover the hill, its very shape transformed
Dialogue: 10,1:14:09.34,1:14:24.13,Song,,0,0,0,,All people look up to it together, Hill 203
Dialogue: 10,1:14:27.86,1:14:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been to the Imperial Headquarters yet? {lit: has Prime Minister ... - I assume that's him}
Dialogue: 10,1:14:29.82,1:14:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I have just come from there.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:32.76,1:14:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,His Majesty went to Imperial Headquarters \Nabout thirty minutes ago, didn't he?
Dialogue: 10,1:14:36.76,1:14:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where has he gone now?
Dialogue: 10,1:14:38.20,1:14:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He is not even in his sitting room.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:56.30,1:14:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:57.16,1:14:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:59.09,1:15:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Big brother, it’s cold over there, so take care.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:03.05,1:15:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be fine.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:04.93,1:15:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Just take care of your health, okay? \NYou don’t have to worry about things at home.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:09.43,1:15:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Son, say goodbye to your father.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:11.91,1:15:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impossible, he doesn't know me yet. {??? maybe doesn't understand or doesn't know how to speak}
Dialogue: 10,1:15:14.13,1:15:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you say that...
Dialogue: 10,1:15:15.31,1:15:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, eat plenty.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:17.18,1:15:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:21.48,1:15:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:23.85,1:15:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You men are going out as well?
Dialogue: 10,1:15:28.60,1:15:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we deploy the day after tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:31.25,1:15:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you said your farewells to your family?
Dialogue: 10,1:15:33.72,1:15:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I have.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:37.83,1:15:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How many are there in your family?
Dialogue: 10,1:15:40.97,1:15:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Only my mother.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:44.61,1:15:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to your father?
Dialogue: 10,1:15:47.65,1:15:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He died ten years ago.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:55.05,1:15:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you said goodbye?
Dialogue: 10,1:15:59.22,1:16:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother is waiting at the camp gate.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:01.28,1:16:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to her at once, don't make her worry.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:05.28,1:16:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I won't worry her!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:08.60,1:16:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on, open it.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:13.60,1:16:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:19.13,1:16:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry along.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:21.31,1:16:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:34.43,1:16:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you take care too.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:36.19,1:16:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch your health!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:38.63,1:16:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:40.80,1:16:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 10,1:16:42.32,1:16:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:47.17,1:16:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:56.61,1:16:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:57.48,1:16:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:58.57,1:16:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay well!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:59.86,1:17:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:00.97,1:17:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, please take care of yourself!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:15.70,1:17:25.00,Song,,0,0,0,,All of them
Dialogue: 10,1:17:25.00,1:17:30.35,Song,,0,0,0,,have gone out
Dialogue: 10,1:17:30.35,1:17:35.94,Song,,0,0,0,,to the army
Dialogue: 10,1:17:35.94,1:17:43.35,Song,,0,0,0,,The old father alone
Dialogue: 10,1:17:43.35,1:17:54.06,Song,,0,0,0,,tends the mountain fields
Dialogue: 10,1:17:57.37,1:17:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Okazawa.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:58.33,1:17:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:00.11,1:18:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to win this war,
Dialogue: 10,1:18:02.97,1:18:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,by any means necessary!
Dialogue: 10,1:18:05.78,1:18:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the people won't forgive us!
Dialogue: 10,1:18:19.28,1:18:23.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Flesh burst like shattered bullets, \Nand bones turned to swords.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:23.35,1:18:30.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Now this Hill 203, watched by the entire world, \Nwas about to be soaked in blood once more.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:50.70,1:18:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:19:04.81,1:19:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise the flag! {????}
Dialogue: 10,1:19:08.17,1:19:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise the national flag!
Dialogue: 10,1:19:11.81,1:19:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise the national flag!
Dialogue: 10,1:19:28.86,1:19:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Excellency, Hill 203 has just fallen.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:31.62,1:19:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It has?
Dialogue: 10,1:19:32.22,1:19:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,1:19:33.42,1:19:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Good... now I can face them.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:50.17,1:19:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,1:19:53.94,1:19:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Extra! Extra! Port Arthur has fallen! Extra!
Dialogue: 10,1:19:58.72,1:20:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Port Arthur has fallen! Extra!
Dialogue: 10,1:20:04.87,1:20:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{Banzai! Banzai!}
Dialogue: 10,1:20:09.76,1:20:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:20:13.64,1:20:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As we greet the New Year, \Nwe respectfully celebrate the surrender of Port Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,1:20:26.72,1:20:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty, who continued to place your trust in Nogi,
Dialogue: 10,1:20:31.72,1:20:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel the deepest shame before you. {for doubting nogi}
Dialogue: 10,1:20:37.42,1:20:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear that Nogi has lost both of his sons.
Dialogue: 10,1:20:45.40,1:20:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Though setting aside personal feelings is the way of a soldier,
Dialogue: 10,1:20:50.83,1:20:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,one can scarcely imagine the sorrow \Nin Commander Nogi's heart.
Dialogue: 10,1:20:56.22,1:21:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Even as enemies, the Russian soldiers \Ndefending Port Arthur fought magnificently.
Dialogue: 10,1:21:04.39,1:21:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Your Majesty has said,
Dialogue: 10,1:21:07.02,1:21:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,war must be guided by justice, \Nonly then is it a glorious sight. {??? 戦いは正義に基づかなければならぬこと、痛快いたしました。}
Dialogue: 10,1:21:15.14,1:21:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the mistaken policies of their country,
Dialogue: 10,1:21:19.03,1:21:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the soldiers under General Stessel \Nfought most bravely until now.
Dialogue: 10,1:21:27.55,1:21:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At the surrender of Port Arthur,
Dialogue: 10,1:21:30.82,1:21:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,see that Nogi is instructed to treat them \Nin a way that preserves a soldier's honor.
Dialogue: 10,1:21:42.20,1:21:57.48,Song,,0,0,0,,With Port Arthur surrendered, the enemy general Stessel meets with General Nogi {https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lA7CK4tQ1F8}
Dialogue: 10,1:21:57.48,1:22:02.72,Song,,0,0,0,,Where is the place of their meeting? At Shuishiying {水師営  - I'm still not sure if it's just "naval camp" or a proper name - Shuishiying. Best I can tell this is the name of a proper place, so lets go with the latter. }
Dialogue: 10,1:22:02.72,1:22:12.59,Song,,0,0,0,,In the yard stands a single jujube tree, its trunk scarred by many bullets
Dialogue: 10,1:22:12.59,1:22:23.09,Song,,0,0,0,,Among the shattered remains of humble houses, the two generals now meet face to face
Dialogue: 10,1:22:25.37,1:22:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, through the united support of the nation, \Neven Port Arthur, said to be impregnable, has at last fallen.
Dialogue: 10,1:22:34.87,1:22:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our army now advances with irresistible force toward Mukden, the enemy's greatest stronghold,
Dialogue: 10,1:22:41.68,1:22:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and its fall also seems near at hand.
Dialogue: 10,1:22:45.15,1:22:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,On behalf of the army, I wish to express our gratitude \Nfor the devoted support of the people.
Dialogue: 10,1:23:10.21,1:23:18.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus Japan with 250,000 men and Russia with 370,000, \Na combined total of 620,000 troops,
Dialogue: 10,1:23:18.78,1:23:25.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,met in the greatest battle in history across a fifty-kilometer front, \Nfought upon the wild plains of Manchuria.
Dialogue: 10,1:23:57.22,1:23:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Run!
Dialogue: 10,1:24:22.36,1:24:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of General Nogi's army has pushed into the western outskirts of Mukden and is fighting street by street!
Dialogue: 10,1:24:27.48,1:24:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 10,1:24:52.75,1:24:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,1:24:55.79,1:25:03.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At last, on March 10th of Meiji 38 (1905), \Nour army entered Mukden.
Dialogue: 10,1:25:28.43,1:25:35.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile the Combined Fleet continued relentless training \Nday and night in preparation to destroy the Baltic Fleet,
Dialogue: 10,1:25:35.38,1:25:39.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the practice target island was battered \Nuntil even its shape was altered.
Dialogue: 10,1:25:48.38,1:25:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In battle it will not be an island. \NThe target moves! We must improve our accuracy!
Dialogue: 10,1:25:52.67,1:25:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:25:53.30,1:25:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them.
Dialogue: 10,1:25:53.97,1:25:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,1:25:56.45,1:25:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, a telegram from the Chief of the Naval General Staff.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:04.98,1:26:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue firing practice!
Dialogue: 10,1:26:07.63,1:26:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Range 8,200!
Dialogue: 10,1:26:09.19,1:26:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Range 8,200.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:11.30,1:26:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Most likely this concerns \Nour operations against the Baltic Fleet.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:15.93,1:26:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,First, regarding the Baltic Fleet, \Nmuch of the information being reported is incorrect,
Dialogue: 10,1:26:20.66,1:26:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so unless great care is taken, \Nsound judgment may become impossible.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:24.32,1:26:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is different from other matters—\NHis Majesty has ordered it.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:28.18,1:26:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I respectfully believe \Nthat His Majesty must be deeply concerned.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:32.31,1:26:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, this is a critical moment.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:34.71,1:26:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Please return by the 21st.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:47.16,1:26:50.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Enemy fleet sighted off Taiwan.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:51.57,1:26:58.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yesterday morning, off Izu Oshima, a merchant steamer \Nof a certain nation was ordered to halt by a Russian destroyer.
Dialogue: 10,1:26:59.17,1:27:06.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At dawn on May 17th, something resembling a Russian torpedo boat \Npassed a point five nautical miles off the Boso coast in Kyushu.
Dialogue: 10,1:27:06.23,1:27:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Second Baltic Fleet joined the Third Fleet \Nat Cam Ranh Bay in French Indochina,
Dialogue: 10,1:27:10.11,1:27:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and since leaving on May 15th, \Nits whereabouts have been unknown.
Dialogue: 10,1:27:13.73,1:27:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Reports published after that are likely false rumors, mere speculation, or perhaps spy activity meant to confuse the operations of our fleet.
Dialogue: 10,1:27:23.29,1:27:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is whether they'll pass through Tsugaru or Tsushima, \Nand where the Combined Fleet should await them.
Dialogue: 10,1:27:28.98,1:27:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to respond quickly to the enemy \Npassing through Tsugaru or Tsushima,
Dialogue: 10,1:27:32.37,1:27:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems best to station the main fleet off the Noto Peninsula.
Dialogue: 10,1:27:36.22,1:27:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the opinion agreed upon \Nby the majority of the Imperial Headquarters staff.
Dialogue: 10,1:27:40.94,1:27:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the opposing opinion?
Dialogue: 10,1:27:43.32,1:27:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That the Baltic Fleet will surely pass through Tsushima, \Nand therefore we should wait at Tsushima.
Dialogue: 10,1:27:50.87,1:27:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Togo has just arrived.
Dialogue: 10,1:28:09.37,1:28:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been some time.
Dialogue: 10,1:28:10.84,1:28:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:28:11.81,1:28:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Togo, are the Combined Fleet's \Ntraining and preparations complete?
Dialogue: 10,1:28:16.38,1:28:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We are continuing our exercises \Nso that there will be no oversight.
Dialogue: 10,1:28:19.88,1:28:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, do you still believe they will come through Tsushima, or do you expect Tsugaru or Soya?
Dialogue: 10,1:28:26.50,1:28:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,With more than 120 ships, \Nwe are searching day and night for the enemy fleet.
Dialogue: 10,1:28:36.54,1:28:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Togo, do you believe we have a chance of victory?
Dialogue: 10,1:28:44.82,1:28:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I pledge that I shall bring you good news.
Dialogue: 10,1:28:48.34,1:28:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I rely on you.
Dialogue: 10,1:28:53.86,1:28:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, was it wise to give such a definite answer? {pledge to win}
Dialogue: 10,1:28:57.95,1:29:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The responsibility is enormous.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:00.72,1:29:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You must have great confidence.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:02.83,1:29:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we were to report the detailed plan before His Majesty, \Nit would only trouble his mind unnecessarily.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:09.80,1:29:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,1:29:10.53,1:29:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No. All sixty-four thousand men of the navy \Nare now burning with the resolve to give their lives in service.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:18.54,1:29:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They are determined to destroy the Baltic Fleet.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:22.09,1:29:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single man expects to return alive.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:25.58,1:29:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If we come back alive, Japan will perish.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:28.73,1:29:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the conviction of every officer and sailor.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:37.51,1:29:44.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A final strategy conference was held \Naboard the flagship Mikasa in Chinhae Bay.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:45.35,1:29:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If such a great fleet is heading for Tsushima, \Nit should already have been sighted by one of our patrol vessels.
Dialogue: 10,1:29:53.74,1:30:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore the enemy fleet may well be planning to break through the Tsugaru Strait in the north in one stroke.
Dialogue: 10,1:30:00.50,1:30:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,However, since we know the enemy has transports waiting at Shanghai, it seems likely they will soon come toward Tsushima.
Dialogue: 10,1:30:07.84,1:30:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is also certain that two of the enemy's light cruisers appeared south of Kyushu and then headed toward the Soya region.
Dialogue: 10,1:30:16.31,1:30:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we cannot determine the enemy's course, the safest plan \Nwould be to gather our main fleet off the Noto Peninsula
Dialogue: 10,1:30:23.07,1:30:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and place patrol forces south of Korea and toward Tsugaru and Soya, \Nthen rush there as soon as the enemy fleet is sighted.
Dialogue: 10,1:30:32.28,1:30:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiting at the Noto Peninsula would certainly allow us \Nto meet the enemy, but the decisive battle would be brief,
Dialogue: 10,1:30:38.29,1:30:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and after a single artillery engagement,\N there is a real danger the enemy might escape to Vladivostok. {meaning they wouldn't arrive in time to properly pound the russian fleet}
Dialogue: 10,1:30:43.56,1:30:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I cannot agree with that plan.
Dialogue: 10,1:30:46.80,1:30:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe we should wait here.
Dialogue: 10,1:30:49.77,1:30:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If we possess the Yamato spirit, \Nthe enemy has the Slavic spirit.
Dialogue: 10,1:30:53.90,1:30:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They will neither flee nor hide, \Nbut surely come to the Tsushima Strait ready for battle.
Dialogue: 10,1:30:58.34,1:31:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I believe it best to wait here as we are.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:01.44,1:31:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially since the Tsugaru and Soya Straits \Nare extremely difficult for a great fleet to pass through.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:06.58,1:31:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot accept that opinion!
Dialogue: 10,1:31:08.32,1:31:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than adopt a one-sided strategy, even with its faults, waiting at the Noto Peninsula seems the only course.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:16.03,1:31:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I was delayed by rough seas.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:17.66,1:31:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work coming.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:18.83,1:31:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Shimamura, \Nopinion is divided about the waiting position.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:23.30,1:31:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Please state your view.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:24.60,1:31:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, it's quite clear, isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,1:31:27.18,1:31:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If the enemy fleet has even one admiral who understands naval warfare, \Nthey come through the Tsushima Strait.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:33.69,1:31:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the Russian fleet knows it cannot enter Vladivostok \Nwithout fighting a decisive battle.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:40.52,1:31:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore the only course left to them is to force their way through the Tsushima Strait, the shortest route to Vladivostok.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:49.17,1:31:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, the Tsushima Strait is nine times wider \Nthan Tsugaru and four and a half times wider than Soya.
Dialogue: 10,1:31:53.73,1:31:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If fortune favors them, they might slip through without being discovered by the Japanese fleet—
Dialogue: 10,1:31:58.44,1:32:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and that would only be possible through Tsushima.
Dialogue: 10,1:32:00.84,1:32:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe we will surely meet them here in decisive battle.
Dialogue: 10,1:32:04.36,1:32:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we should ask Admiral Togo for the final decision.
Dialogue: 10,1:32:11.26,1:32:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, please.
Dialogue: 10,1:32:16.02,1:32:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire fleet will remain here and wait.
Dialogue: 10,1:32:32.75,1:32:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we request an imperial order \Nto {have the Combined Fleet }wait at the Noto Peninsula?
Dialogue: 10,1:32:35.91,1:32:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait one more day before asking his majesty. {for an imperial command}
Dialogue: 10,1:32:43.21,1:32:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Any messages from the fleet?
Dialogue: 10,1:32:44.52,1:32:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,None.
Dialogue: 10,1:32:52.37,1:32:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If the enemy gains control of the sea, \Nhundreds of thousands of our army in Manchuria will be isolated.
Dialogue: 10,1:32:57.79,1:32:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we request an imperial order?
Dialogue: 10,1:32:59.73,1:33:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,His Majesty has entrusted the matter to Admiral Togo.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:02.36,1:33:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the moment when Japan will either rise or fall.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:05.51,1:33:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief of the Naval {General }Staff,
Dialogue: 10,1:33:07.54,1:33:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as we saw in the case of Commander Nogi, \NHis Majesty's judgment of men is truly keen.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:13.35,1:33:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We should entrust it to Togo.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:20.90,1:33:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okazawa.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:21.63,1:33:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:24.47,1:33:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the Naval Ministry sent any word?
Dialogue: 10,1:33:28.19,1:33:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet, sir. What shall we do \Nif it comes in the middle of the night?
Dialogue: 10,1:33:32.61,1:33:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not matter, inform me at once.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:37.01,1:33:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:38.03,1:33:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty, I am certain good news will come.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:48.21,1:33:56.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On May 27{does this need -th? What I found was that in formal writting you avoid the "th"}, the auxiliary cruiser \NShinano Maru was patrolling near Jeju Island.
Dialogue: 10,1:33:57.50,1:34:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen degrees to port! \NAppears to be ship lights!
Dialogue: 10,1:34:06.87,1:34:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen degrees to port?
Dialogue: 10,1:34:07.98,1:34:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,1:34:08.80,1:34:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What time?
Dialogue: 10,1:34:09.83,1:34:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,2:45.
Dialogue: 10,1:34:31.95,1:34:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears to be a Russian hospital ship.
Dialogue: 10,1:34:33.96,1:34:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Any other vessels in sight?
Dialogue: 10,1:34:35.38,1:34:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see signal lights!
Dialogue: 10,1:34:37.74,1:34:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! That is definitely a signal light. \NThe enemy fleet must be nearby.
Dialogue: 10,1:34:52.82,1:34:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, I can see them!
Dialogue: 10,1:34:54.58,1:34:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the enemy fleet. \NWhat time is it now?
Dialogue: 10,1:34:57.98,1:34:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,4:45.
Dialogue: 10,1:34:59.55,1:35:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to report the sighting! {of the enemy fleet}
Dialogue: 10,1:35:01.51,1:35:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 10,1:35:20.14,1:35:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention!
Dialogue: 10,1:35:23.21,1:35:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All hands assemble on deck!
Dialogue: 10,1:35:34.96,1:35:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Signal from Shinano Maru: enemy fleet sighted.
Dialogue: 10,1:35:38.82,1:35:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Report says they are heading toward the Tsushima Strait!
Dialogue: 10,1:35:44.57,1:35:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All squadrons, sortie immediately.
Dialogue: 10,1:35:47.01,1:35:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All squadrons, put to sea at once.
Dialogue: 10,1:35:55.77,1:36:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that all of you, working together in unity, \Nwill bring this glorious battle to a successful end.
Dialogue: 10,1:36:04.06,1:36:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to sail!
Dialogue: 10,1:36:06.48,1:36:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Move out!
Dialogue: 10,1:36:08.02,1:36:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Move out!
Dialogue: 10,1:36:43.42,1:36:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,6:31 a.m., signal sent from the flagship Mikasa.
Dialogue: 10,1:36:47.04,1:36:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At 5:45 a.m. on May 27th, the cruiser Shinano Maru \Nreported sighting the enemy fleet at position 456.
Dialogue: 10,1:36:55.16,1:36:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The Combined Fleet has immediately sortied to destroy it.
Dialogue: 10,1:36:58.97,1:37:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Today the weather is fine, but the seas are high.
Dialogue: 10,1:37:49.92,1:37:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All ships ready for battle!
Dialogue: 10,1:37:51.99,1:37:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 10,1:37:52.80,1:37:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, the enemy fleet is in sight.
Dialogue: 10,1:37:55.13,1:37:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy fleet sighted!
Dialogue: 10,1:37:58.53,1:38:03.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At 1:40 p.m., the Combined Fleet finally caught sight
Dialogue: 10,1:38:03.02,1:38:11.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of the entire Baltic Fleet, thirty-eight ships strong, \Nwith the flagship Suvorov at its head.
Dialogue: 10,1:38:12.83,1:38:20.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Leading this great fleet to battle against ours \Nwas Vice Admiral Rozhestvensky.
Dialogue: 10,1:38:27.33,1:38:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, the Z flag has been raised. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Z_flag#Military_uses}
Dialogue: 10,1:38:29.20,1:38:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, signal it to the ship!
Dialogue: 10,1:38:31.09,1:38:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The empire's fate depends on the result of this battle, \Nlet every man do his utmost duty!
Dialogue: 10,1:38:48.86,1:38:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, the Z flag has been raised on the Mikasa.
Dialogue: 10,1:39:02.19,1:39:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Range twelve thousand!
Dialogue: 10,1:39:08.61,1:39:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve thousand! \NThe enemy is close.
Dialogue: 10,1:39:11.30,1:39:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve thousand!
Dialogue: 10,1:39:12.54,1:39:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve thousand.
Dialogue: 10,1:39:13.70,1:39:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve thousand!
Dialogue: 10,1:39:16.15,1:39:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve thousand!
Dialogue: 10,1:39:18.04,1:39:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Eleven thousand!
Dialogue: 10,1:39:20.82,1:39:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Shells ready.
Dialogue: 10,1:39:33.12,1:39:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready, safety off!
Dialogue: 10,1:39:35.66,1:39:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Range ten thousand.
Dialogue: 10,1:39:36.66,1:39:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Range ten thousand!
Dialogue: 10,1:39:41.73,1:39:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Light the boilers.
Dialogue: 10,1:39:42.55,1:39:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Light the boilers!
Dialogue: 10,1:39:50.34,1:39:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, how is the position? {??}
Dialogue: 10,1:39:53.71,1:39:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As planned.
Dialogue: 10,1:39:58.51,1:40:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Range eight thousand five hundred!
Dialogue: 10,1:40:03.10,1:40:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief of Staff, if we continue like this, we will \Npass them head-on and exchange only a short artillery duel. {???}
Dialogue: 10,1:40:08.39,1:40:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, I advise parallel courses. \NI recommend turning left 180 degrees.
Dialogue: 10,1:40:15.73,1:40:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Execute the turn.
Dialogue: 10,1:40:18.22,1:40:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief of Staff, a turn?
Dialogue: 10,1:40:20.54,1:40:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Left turn!
Dialogue: 10,1:40:22.52,1:40:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hard to port!
Dialogue: 10,1:40:23.81,1:40:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hard to port.
Dialogue: 10,1:40:25.07,1:40:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead ship to port!
Dialogue: 10,1:40:26.21,1:40:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead ship to port.
Dialogue: 10,1:40:27.74,1:40:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Range eight thousand.
Dialogue: 10,1:40:29.91,1:40:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward lead! {前先頭 = forward head/ahead vanguard - if that transcript is to be believed - I personally have no idea what they're saying/meaning}
Dialogue: 10,1:40:31.51,1:40:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward lead.
Dialogue: 10,1:40:34.83,1:40:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward lead!
Dialogue: 10,1:40:38.14,1:40:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward lead!
Dialogue: 10,1:40:39.29,1:40:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Men, to the forward guns! {??????}
Dialogue: 10,1:40:41.59,1:40:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward lead!
Dialogue: 10,1:40:48.10,1:40:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Togo is out of his mind! \NCrush the Japanese fleet!
Dialogue: 10,1:40:52.23,1:40:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}But of course! Let's crush them!
Dialogue: 10,1:41:13.59,1:41:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To the aft guns! {??????}
Dialogue: 10,1:41:16.06,1:41:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Man the aft! {????????}
Dialogue: 10,1:41:23.43,1:41:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mikasa is maneuvering to avoid being hit! {????????}
Dialogue: 10,1:41:26.13,1:41:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A successive turn?
Dialogue: 10,1:41:27.47,1:41:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad—making a great turn right before the enemy!
Dialogue: 10,1:41:30.18,1:41:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the only way to do it.
Dialogue: 10,1:41:32.34,1:41:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew the risk from the start.
Dialogue: 10,1:41:53.83,1:41:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All guns ready for action! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,1:41:56.93,1:41:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Range seven thousand!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:08.38,1:42:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Range six thousand six hundred!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:10.11,1:42:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Target set! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,1:42:11.78,1:42:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Range 6,600!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:13.58,1:42:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Target set!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:15.45,1:42:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Range 6,600.
Dialogue: 10,1:42:17.02,1:42:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, they're firing heavily now.
Dialogue: 10,1:42:20.82,1:42:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, has the order to fire been given yet?!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:23.13,1:42:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, wait, wait!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:25.93,1:42:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Range 8,000.
Dialogue: 10,1:42:27.33,1:42:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Range 8,000!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:28.66,1:42:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Still no order to attack?
Dialogue: 10,1:42:31.93,1:42:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mikasa's in danger.
Dialogue: 10,1:42:42.04,1:42:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Range 6,000.
Dialogue: 10,1:42:45.28,1:42:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Commence bombardment.
Dialogue: 10,1:42:47.25,1:42:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Begin firing!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:48.62,1:42:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Begin firing!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:52.44,1:42:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Target: Suvorov! Fire!
Dialogue: 10,1:42:55.84,1:42:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Commence bombardment!
Dialogue: 10,1:43:35.60,1:43:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, the Mikasa's taken two or three hits! \NIs the commander-in-chief all right? {not sure, maybe c-in-c is this guy he's talking to}
Dialogue: 10,1:43:40.14,1:43:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,With nerves like his, \Nthe shells themselves might run away! {meaning that they're so undisturbed that the shells should be scared}
Dialogue: 10,1:43:42.87,1:43:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy flagship is on fire!
Dialogue: 10,1:43:46.88,1:43:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Once our formation's complete, \Nwe'll finish them off!
Dialogue: 10,1:43:56.65,1:43:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please move inside the conning tower.
Dialogue: 10,1:43:59.59,1:44:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll command from right here.
Dialogue: 10,1:44:01.52,1:44:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, direct hit on the Suvorov!
Dialogue: 10,1:44:17.47,1:44:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy ship's burning! Keep firing!
Dialogue: 10,1:44:23.38,1:44:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Concentrated fire! {????????}
Dialogue: 10,1:44:32.89,1:44:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{????????? feel free to make anything at all up, paul, I can't hear a thing}
Dialogue: 10,1:44:34.92,1:44:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{same, only the last parts are the same}
Dialogue: 10,1:44:38.89,1:44:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{Ah!}
Dialogue: 10,1:44:40.40,1:44:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, fire!
Dialogue: 10,1:44:42.46,1:44:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not dead yet! Keep firing! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,1:44:45.01,1:44:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 10,1:44:46.54,1:44:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine, sir!
Dialogue: 10,1:44:47.90,1:44:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Take over for him! Move!
Dialogue: 10,1:44:49.97,1:44:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine, sir!
Dialogue: 10,1:44:55.66,1:44:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! Direct hit! Massive fires! {??????????}
Dialogue: 10,1:44:58.28,1:44:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 10,1:45:21.95,1:45:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Shoot! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,1:45:24.64,1:45:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Reload it! {???????}
Dialogue: 10,1:45:26.91,1:45:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Hurry up! {скорее?}
Dialogue: 10,1:45:32.91,1:45:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Hurry up! {скорее?}
Dialogue: 10,1:45:36.15,1:45:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Hurry up! {скорее?}
Dialogue: 10,1:45:37.89,1:45:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{???? none of actors are actually russian I imagine so their take on things that they supposed a russian man would say make me suicidal}
Dialogue: 10,1:45:39.59,1:45:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}We need to beat them quickly! {бить их скорее надо, бить их?}
Dialogue: 10,1:45:41.26,1:45:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Return fire! Hurry! {???}
Dialogue: 10,1:45:48.53,1:45:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Evacuate the section! Hurry, hurry! {??????????}
Dialogue: 10,1:46:02.19,1:46:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:46:04.41,1:46:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, did you see that? \NThe shells you fired hit their mark!
Dialogue: 10,1:46:09.28,1:46:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see it?
Dialogue: 10,1:46:12.13,1:46:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 10,1:46:13.05,1:46:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Banzai! Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,1:46:29.08,1:46:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Suvorov appears to be dead in the water.
Dialogue: 10,1:46:38.88,1:46:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're hit on starboard! {???????}
Dialogue: 10,1:46:40.58,1:46:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the fire brigade here! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,1:46:42.12,1:46:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:46:43.99,1:46:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:46:46.29,1:46:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:46:49.56,1:46:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The fire on board is localized! {???????}
Dialogue: 10,1:46:51.66,1:46:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the position?
Dialogue: 10,1:46:52.70,1:46:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As planned!
Dialogue: 10,1:46:53.63,1:46:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, a Russian ship is sinking!
Dialogue: 10,1:47:15.30,1:47:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:47:18.82,1:47:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:47:33.60,1:47:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H1D541F&}Load it! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,1:47:38.04,1:47:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,1:47:50.60,1:47:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Signal transmitted from the flagship Mikasa, \N7:00 p.m., May 27.
Dialogue: 10,1:47:54.64,1:48:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Combined Fleet engaged the enemy fleet near Okinoshima, \Nand by 6:00 p.m. today has sunk at least four enemy battleships,
Dialogue: 10,1:48:02.08,1:48:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,inflicting heavy damage on many others.
Dialogue: 10,1:48:04.00,1:48:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Our own losses are negligible. Furthermore, the destroyer squadrons and torpedo units
Dialogue: 10,1:48:07.55,1:48:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,will launch night attacks \Non the remaining enemy ships after sunset.
Dialogue: 10,1:48:12.17,1:48:18.65,Song,,0,0,0,,Surrounded on every side by the seas, our Shikishima, our Akitsushima
Dialogue: 10,1:48:18.65,1:48:24.85,Song,,0,0,0,,To guard against enemies beyond our shores, batteries on land, warships at sea
Dialogue: 10,1:48:24.85,1:48:31.16,Song,,0,0,0,,Even if our bodies sink beneath the waves, loyal men will never retreat
Dialogue: 10,1:48:31.16,1:48:37.91,Song,,0,0,0,,With hearts of ironclad resolve, how could such defenders ever be broken?
Dialogue: 10,1:48:43.79,1:49:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{?????? I can only hear "...our motherland, our motherland" - if that's an actual song, I'm not finding it}
Dialogue: 10,1:49:38.51,1:49:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, as the enemy flagship and the other warships sunk,
Dialogue: 10,1:49:43.30,1:49:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's said their officers and men sang their national anthem and went down with their ships. {yeah, safe to assume they made it up, the anthem at the time was https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/God_Save_the_Tsar! and it's nothing like that}
Dialogue: 10,1:49:53.88,1:49:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnificent.
Dialogue: 10,1:50:00.85,1:50:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus the battle unfolded over the 27th and 28th.
Dialogue: 10,1:50:04.72,1:50:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Of roughly 38 enemy vessels, 20 were sunk,
Dialogue: 10,1:50:08.62,1:50:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,5 captured, and 8 destroyed,
Dialogue: 10,1:50:11.47,1:50:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Combined Fleet annihilated the Baltic Fleet.
Dialogue: 10,1:50:14.61,1:50:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile our own losses \Nwere no more than three torpedo boats.
Dialogue: 10,1:50:18.77,1:50:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In this great war, the enemy's strength \Nwas not too different from our own.
Dialogue: 10,1:50:21.92,1:50:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Their officers and men also fought \Nwith all their might for their homeland.
Dialogue: 10,1:50:25.97,1:50:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet the reason our Combined Fleet was able to secure victory \Nlies solely in the august virtue of His Majesty the Emperor,
Dialogue: 10,1:50:33.18,1:50:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and the officers and men, whether living or fallen in battle, \Nupon witnessing this result are overcome with emotion,
Dialogue: 10,1:50:39.73,1:50:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as though they have no words to express it.
Dialogue: 10,1:50:43.97,1:50:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the people of the nation hear this joyful news at once,
Dialogue: 10,1:50:49.74,1:50:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and convey words of appreciation to the Combined Fleet.
Dialogue: 10,1:50:55.30,1:51:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Combined Fleet intercepted \Nthe enemy in the Korea Strait,
Dialogue: 10,1:51:00.41,1:51:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and after days of fierce fighting, finally annihilated them, \Nachieving an unprecedented glory.
Dialogue: 10,1:51:06.01,1:51:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I rejoice that through the loyal bravery of our men, \Nwe have answered the spirits of our imperial ancestors.
Dialogue: 10,1:51:11.89,1:51:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{Banzai! Banzai!}
Dialogue: 10,1:51:19.66,1:51:25.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Through the united determination of the entire nation, \Ncentered upon Emperor Meiji,
Dialogue: 10,1:51:25.43,1:51:29.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,this great war ended in a miraculous victory,
Dialogue: 10,1:51:29.10,1:51:35.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and Japan, once merely an island nation, \Nsuddenly stood among the great powers of the world.
Dialogue: 10,1:51:36.56,1:51:45.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Now we must unite the pride and strength of the Japanese people and contribute to the future development of peace in the world.
Dialogue: 10,1:51:46.07,1:51:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 10,1:52:17.66,1:52:42.54,Song,,0,0,0,,Since ancient times, in wars such as these, countless lives have been lost
